column16: Operates a helpline for South Asian women victims of domestic violence. column14: Operates nightly shelter for young adults, ages 18-25. Provides clients with clean bedding and sheets; dinner and hot breakfast; laundry, showers, and health and hygiene supplies. Shelter entrance is at the SW corner of the church.
column15: Operates nightly shelter for young adults, AGES 18 THROUGH 25. Also refers clients to the Catalyst at Straley House pre-transitional living program.
column16: Operates nightly shelter for young adults, ages 18 through 25. Provides a hot dinner and breakfast. Also refers clients to the Catalyst at Straley House pre-transitional living program. Walk in or call between 8pm and 8:30pm, to get on the list.

column5: *Main Site - TeamChild
column11: Legal Services and Advocacy for Youth
column13: Legal Services and Advocacy for Youth
column14: Provides advocacy & access to community-based services for youth, 12-18, who are in, or at risk of involvement in, the juvenile justice system. Staff will eventually need to speak with youth directly. Call 2-1-1 for initial screening.
column15: Provides advocacy and access to community-based services for youth, ages 12 through 18, who are in, or at high risk of involvement in, the juvenile justice system. Staff will eventually need to speak with the youth directly.
column16: Provides advocacy and access to community-based services for youth, ages 12 through 18, who are in, or at high risk of involvement in the juvenile justice system. Callers themselves must be youth, ages 12 through 18 or their parent or guardian. TeamChild will eventually need to speak directly to the youth.  TeamChild attorneys work to secure community-based services, helping youth address underlying issues contributing to their criminal or behavioral troubles. Does not provide criminal defense representation to youth or adults involved in either the juvenile delinquency system or the adult criminal system. Call 211 for screening.
